race.comment: SIR ARTIE (14) was most impressive winning two back over 1400m at Rosehill then copped a heavy bump at the top of the lane and can be forgiven for finishing fifth last start, again over seven furlongs at Rosehill. Rock hard fit and looks hard to beat, with the final 100m the only slight concern. WELL TIMED (15) caught the eye two back at Rosehill in the same race as SIR ARTIE then disappointed on Cup Day at Randwick when firm favourite. Best form is right up there so must be respected if they back up in four days. MELODY AGAIN (9) missed the kick and was never a hope in the Kosciuszko although she did pass quite a few in the straight. Has an excellent second-up record so with even luck a big run is on the cards. OVERRIDING (12) hasn't won for a long while but is a winner at this trip from one try. No surprise to see sharp improvement. HARLEM QUEEN (11) got too far back first-up in the Silver Eagle. Good enough to test this field if she brings her A-game.
